Raggedy Ann is a character created by American writer Johnny Gruelle -LRB- 1880 -- 1938 -RRB- in a series of books he wrote and illustrated for young children .
Raggedy Ann is a rag doll with red yarn for hair and has a triangle nose .
Johnny Gruelle received US Patent D47789 for his Raggedy Ann doll on September 7 , 1915 .
The character was created in 1915 as a doll , and was introduced to the public in the 1918 book Raggedy Ann Stories .
When a doll was marketed with the book , the concept had great success .
A sequel , Raggedy Andy Stories -LRB- 1920 -RRB- , introduced the character of her brother , Raggedy Andy .